James de Villiers, News24 (Supplied by ER24) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Durban &ndash; A 32-year-old man was seriously injured after a gate fell on him at an apartment building in Clermont, Durban, paramedics said.&nbsp;It is understood that the man had had been working on the roller gate when it fell on him, ER24 spokesperson Russel Meiring said in a statement. When paramedics arrived, the man was found lying next to the gate surrounded by colleagues.&nbsp;Advanced life support interventions were applied by paramedics on scene.The man was taken to a nearby hospital for further medical attention.&nbsp;24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.